          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "AMS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Stacks of up to three foils were bombarded with",
                "protons. After the irradiation, known amounts of 27A1",
                "powder (15-25 mg Al) were added to each of the 26Mg",
                "foils. It is assumed that the 26Al produced in the",
                "26Mg foils is converted to Al203 with the same",
                "efficiency as the added 27Al. The MgO + Al203 powder",
                " (16-40 mg) was then thoroughly mixed with 140 mg Zn",
                "powder and pressed to solid pellets of 6.4 mm",
                "diameter, which were mounted to the 10-position cone",
                "wheel of the inverted Cs-beam sputter source at the",
                "Argonne tandem. The split-pole focal plane detector",
                "is a position sensitive ionization chamber which",
                "generates position, differential energy loss and",
                "total energy signals, thus allowing complete mass and",
                "nuclear charge identification."
              ]
            }
          ],
